Class Register

java.lang.Object
  Emulator.Components.Component
      Emulator.Components.Register
All Implemented Interfaces:
DataComponent, Constants
Direct Known Subclasses:
AddressRegister, DataRegister, IORegister
public abstract class Register
extends Component
implements DataComponent

********************** Created By: Yuval Tzur Date: 14/12/12 Time: 21:27 Description: This is the register class. It defines all the methods and members each register must have. All registers will inherit from this class. A register is a component. Members defined by this class are the register's value and the write enable flag. Each register has a value buffer to mimic the master-slave functionality of real flip-flops. Values are set to the buffer and read from the value. An update method will move the value from the buffer to the value. Values can be set only if the write enable flag is true. ***********************
